<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Egg</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">8</figureCitation>
). Fusiform; yellowish, gradually becoming dark brown over time; about 152 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 69 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, found deposited randomly on lower surface of leaves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicName genus="Puparium" lsidName="Puparium" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Puparium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Covered by a thin layer of white wax (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">3</figureCitation>
); puparium in early stage white (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">5</figureCitation>
), gradually turns black (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">4</figureCitation>
), about 926-1120 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 763-832 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide; elliptical, broadest at the transverse molting suture region; posteriorly horizontal.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474327" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" start="Figures 9–12" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Figures 9-12.</emphasis>
Scanning electron microscope (SEM) photographs of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. schimae" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="schimae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">A. schimae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">9</emphasis>
puparium, dorsal view 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">10</emphasis>
margin 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">11</emphasis>
vasiform 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">orifice</taxonomicName>
and operculum 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">12</emphasis>
third instar nymph.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Margin</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) photographs of A. schimae sp. nov. 9 puparium, dorsal view 10 margin 11 vasiform orifice and operculum 12 third instar nymph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474327" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–15" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 15. Aleuroclava schimae, sp. nov., slide mounted specimen. 13 puparium, dorsal view 14 margin 15 vasiform orifice and operculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures13-15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474328" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Aleuroclava schimae sp. nov., holotype puparium, China, Zhejiang. 16 puparium, dorsal (right) and ventral (left) views 17 margin 18 vasiform orifice." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474329" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">17</figureCitation>
). Crenulate, 0.1 mm wide, 23-28 crenulations. Paired anterior and posterior marginal setae 27 and 16 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, respectively. Thoracic tracheal pore area slightly recessed and emarginated at margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Dorsum</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Almost flat, slightly raised on abdomen; without tubercles. Submargin demarcated from the dorsal disc by a faint line. Longitudinal moulting suture reaching anterior margin and the transverse moulting suture reaching submargin (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–15" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 15. Aleuroclava schimae, sp. nov., slide mounted specimen. 13 puparium, dorsal view 14 margin 15 vasiform orifice and operculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures13-15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474328" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Aleuroclava schimae sp. nov., holotype puparium, China, Zhejiang. 16 puparium, dorsal (right) and ventral (left) views 17 margin 18 vasiform orifice." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474329" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">16</figureCitation>
). Thoracic and abdominal segment sutures well defined. Middle length of abdominal segment I 53 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; segment II 47 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; segments III-VI subequal, 37 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; segment VII 28 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. Geminate pores present (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) photographs of A. schimae sp. nov. 9 puparium, dorsal view 10 margin 11 vasiform orifice and operculum 12 third instar nymph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474327" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–15" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 15. Aleuroclava schimae, sp. nov., slide mounted specimen. 13 puparium, dorsal view 14 margin 15 vasiform orifice and operculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures13-15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474328" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Aleuroclava schimae sp. nov., holotype puparium, China, Zhejiang. 16 puparium, dorsal (right) and ventral (left) views 17 margin 18 vasiform orifice." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474329" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">16</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Chaetotaxy</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Cephalic, first, eighth abdominal and caudal setae 9, 13, 4 and 47 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, respectively. Eighth abdominal setae located below the base of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">orifice</taxonomicName>
. Caudal furrow 68 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long. 
<taxonomicName genus="Vasiform" lsidName="Vasiform orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Vasiform orifice</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) photographs of A. schimae sp. nov. 9 puparium, dorsal view 10 margin 11 vasiform orifice and operculum 12 third instar nymph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474327" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–15" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 13 - 15. Aleuroclava schimae, sp. nov., slide mounted specimen. 13 puparium, dorsal view 14 margin 15 vasiform orifice and operculum." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures13-15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474328" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">15</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Aleuroclava schimae sp. nov., holotype puparium, China, Zhejiang. 16 puparium, dorsal (right) and ventral (left) views 17 margin 18 vasiform orifice." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474329" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">18</figureCitation>
). Cordate to subcircular, slightly longer than wide, 48 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 44 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, lateral margins rounded, basal ends being curved to meet basal margin; operculum cordate, 33 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 29 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, almost covering the 
<taxonomicName genus="Vasiform" lsidName="orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">orifice</taxonomicName>
and obscuring the lingula. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Venter</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Thoracic and caudal tracheal folds discernible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Aleuroclava schimae sp. nov., holotype puparium, China, Zhejiang. 16 puparium, dorsal (right) and ventral (left) views 17 margin 18 vasiform orifice." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474329" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">16</figureCitation>
). Ventral abdominal setae placed on anterior to vasiform 
<taxonomicName genus="Vasiform" lsidName="orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">orifice</taxonomicName>
, 6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 49 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
apart. Antennae extending near the base of prolegs. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Third instar nymph</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) photographs of A. schimae sp. nov. 9 puparium, dorsal view 10 margin 11 vasiform orifice and operculum 12 third instar nymph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474327" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">12</figureCitation>
). Light yellow, body transparent, elliptical, about 720 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 540 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide; eye spots obvious. 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Second instar nymph</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 3–8" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 3 - 8. Habitus, developmental stages of A. schimae sp. nov., on S. superba. 3, 4 puparium, late stage 5 puparium, early stage 6 third instar 7 second instar 8 eggs." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.991.47725.figures3-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/474326" pageId="0" pageNumber="121">7</figureCitation>
): yellowish, elongate-elliptical, about 290 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 170 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide; transparent wax secretion along the body margin, about 11 
